Sashiko Carhartt Work Jacket

This vintage Carhartt jacket has been repaired in a Sashiko Style. Sashiko is a Japanese form of repair and translates directly as “little stabs”. It is typically carried out with a white cotton thread on indigo fabric and this visible mending technique has been practised in Japan for thousands of years.

Most of the repairs can be found around the cuffs, sleeves and on the hood while other areas have been left frayed, giving it a really nice vintage look.
